The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 Mumbai, May 4: RBI deputy governor Rakesh Mohan has resigned and will take up an assignment at the Stanford University in the United States. RBI sources said the deputy governor has put in his papers, but will not quit the central bank immediately. Rakesh Mohan has been offered an appointment as the distinguished consulting professor at the Stanford Centre for International Development at Stanford University, the RBI said.                             
	 New Delhi, May 4: The Cellular Operators Association of India will set up 1,600 centres in the country for installing genuine international mobile equipment identity (IMEI) numbers in devices that dont have them.                             
	 New Delhi, May 4: The Supreme Court has ruled that an insurance company cannot issue a policy at a future date without the consent of the insured.                             
	 New Delhi, May 4: An inter-ministerial task force has suggested that the government act proactively to strengthen the pharma industry. It warned of takeover threats for most drug makers by their large foreign peers.                             
	 Calcutta, May 4: Kesoram Industries today reported a 50 per cent jump in net profit at Rs 159.22 crore in the fourth quarter ended March 2009, compared with the same period last year. The companys turnover during the period was at Rs 1,175.77 crore.                                                                                                                           
